<Class name="CM_DeckItemLayout" id="ba0db0c7-895b-4c5b-b6c9-4077faacc90e">
    <superclass name="CM_LayoutGraphic"/>
    <persistentAllowed/>
    <sharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassPersistentAllowed/>
    <subclassSharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassTransientAllowed/>
    <transientAllowed/>
    <text>

SCALE
####

1 foot = 3 pixels
8 feet = 24 pixels
20 feet = 60 pixels
40 feet = 120 pixels

1 metre = 10 pixels
6 metre = 60 pixels (20 feet)
2.4 metre = 24 pixels (8 feet)

The polygons are the layout and so are stored in centimetres. These are converted to pixels.

10 centimetres = 1 pixel; ROROStructurePixelsPerMetre

COVERED
######

Container positions may be 'covered' by upto 4 different types of GC layout.

The GC Type Graphic will have one of the following types:

DeckItemLayoutType_CCLoad - Load Colour Coding for a GC Area
DeckItemLayoutType_CCDischarge - Discharge Colour Coding for a GC Area
DeckItemLayoutType_GCLoad - Load Defn, which has a  location controller, for a GC Area
DeckItemLayoutType_GCDischarge - Discharge Defn, which has a  location controller, for a GC Area

Depending on the view in JMT we will 'hide', i.e. not draw, the container positions.

</text>
    <DbClassMap file="vesselStructures"/>
    <ExplicitInverseRef name="allCoveredPolygons" id="b65bf9b7-2ba1-4be1-94e0-f900558df8ca">
